\begin_layout Standard
Suppose that you are discretizing the 1d Schrodinger wave equation (nondimension
alized and with zero potential): 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=i\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial x^{2}}+iVu,
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $V(x)$
\end_inset

 is a real-valued function.
 Suppose that we discretize in space at intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x$
\end_inset

 and in time with some timestep 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta t$
\end_inset

, denoting 
\begin_inset Formula $u(m\Delta x,n\Delta t)\approx u_{m}^{n}$
\end_inset

 as in class.
 We will discretize 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial^{2}/\partial x^{2}$
\end_inset

 with the usual center-difference approximation 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{u_{m+1}-2u_{m}+u_{m-1}}{\Delta x^{2}}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $Vu$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{m}u_{m}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{m}=V(m\Delta x$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

