\begin_layout Subsection*
Problem 2: Discretizing a 2d wave equation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider the scalar wave equation with constant coefficients, which can
 be written as in the notes as two coupled equations 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=\nabla\cdot\vec{v}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\vec{v}}{\partial t}=\nabla u$
\end_inset

.
 Now, let us consider this in two dimensions (for an infinite spatial domain
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega=\mathbb{R}^{2}$
\end_inset

, don't worry about boundary conditions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose that we discretize 
\begin_inset Formula $u(x,y,t)$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n}\approx u(m_{x}\Delta x,m_{y}\Delta y,n\Delta t)$
\end_inset

 for integers 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{x},m_{y},n$
\end_inset

.
 Explain how (i.e.
 where/when) we should discretize 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{x}(x,y,t)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{y}(x,y,t)$
\end_inset

 so that our equations 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=\nabla\cdot\vec{v}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\vec{v}}{\partial t}=\nabla u$
\end_inset

 can all be implemented as explicit center differences, similar to the staggered
-grid leap-frog scheme in class for the 1d case.
 Give the discretized equations.
 (Hint: 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{x}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{y}$
\end_inset

 don't have to be discretized on the same spatial grid.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Combine your discretized equations back into a discretization of 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial t^{2}}=\nabla^{2}u$
\end_inset

, as in class, by writing: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial t^{2}}\approx\frac{u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n+1}-2u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n}+u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n-1}}{\Delta t^{2}}=\frac{\frac{u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n+1}-u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n}}{\Delta t}-\frac{u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n}-u_{m_{x},m_{y}}^{n-1}}{\Delta t}}{\Delta t}=\cdots,
\]

\end_inset

where the right-hand side is some spatial derivatives (finite differences)
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

.
 (Do 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 re-discretize 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial t^{2}}=\nabla^{2}u$
\end_inset

 from the beginning; make sure you plug in your discretizations from the
 previous part.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Using the previous part (which helpfully is only in terms of 
